sentence: Exhibit 99.1 Lexington, MA June 6, 2011 Agenus Inc. (NASDAQ: AGEN), a leading developer of therapeutic vaccines for cancer and infectious diseases, today announced results from a Phase 2 clinical trial testing the Prophage Series G-200 vaccine (HSPPC-96; vitespen) in deadly recurrent brain cancer  glioblastoma multiforme (GBM)  in a poster presentation at the 47th Annual Meeting of the American Society of Clinical Oncology (ASCO) in Chicago, Illinois.
